Residents are not backing down. They are threatening to block the N3 freeway. eNCA's Manqoba Mchunu reports. Courtesy #DStv403 HARRISMITH - Enraged Harrismith residents say they want out of their municipality and are threatening to block the N3. They have taken to the streets for the third day of a shutdown over service delivery issues at the Maluti-A-Phofung Municipality in the Free State. READ: N3 Highway in Harrismith cleared after protest This comes after the deputy president visited the embattled municipality last week, promising better service. The municipality has been identified as one of the hotspots in the country for service delivery problems. * eNCA's Manqoba Mchunu reports.